{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents"],"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games","generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"importable unit of "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GamePlugin","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s8SendableP","text":"Sendable","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A plugin bundles the player-typeable vocabulary a system needs ("},{"code":"buy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"attack","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"ask","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") with the logic that reacts to it, so the system can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shipped once and reused instead of hand-copied into every game."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct CommercePlugin: GamePlugin {","    static let buy = Intent(\"buy\")","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {","        SyntaxRule(\"buy\", slots: .direct, intent: Self.buy)","    }","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Logic-only: a plugin owns no state","anchor":"Logic-only-a-plugin-owns-no-state","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" bundle, a plugin is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}]},{"type":"text","text":" reflected by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bootstrap, so it declares no rooms, items, or "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" state of its own. It"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operates entirely over entities and globals the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"host"}]},{"type":"text","text":" declares, receiving"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"what it needs as parameters. That keeps a plugin portable: it makes no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assumptions about the host’s world beyond the traits and intents it agrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on. A plugin that genuinely needs to ship its own content is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" bundle instead (list it in the game’s "},{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"The host opts in by splicing","anchor":"The-host-opts-in-by-splicing","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host stores the plugin as a plain property and splices its vocabulary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and rules into its own blocks. "},{"code":"verbs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" merges just like a game’s own, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the plugin’s rule factories return "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" the host composes in:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct LampShop: Game {","    let commerce = CommercePlugin()","    @Global var purse = Purse(coins: 10)","    let lantern = Item { name(\"brass lantern\"); trait(\"price\", 5) }","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { commerce.verbs }","    var rules: Rules {","        commerce.purchase(of: lantern,","                          balance: { purse.coins },","                          charge:  { purse.coins -= $0 })","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The protocol’s own "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin\/rules","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" requirement carries only self-contained,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"world-scoped rules that need nothing from the host. Rules that must reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host entities are exposed as "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"parameterized methods"}]},{"type":"text","text":" returning "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"code":"purchase(of:balance:charge:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" above), which the host calls with its own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declarations — every line still readable in the host’s source."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin\/rules","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin\/verbs"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GamePlugin","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"title":"GamePlugin","roleHeading":"Protocol","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:6Gnusto10GamePluginP"},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Plugins":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Plugins","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Content Bundles","abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin/verbs":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Player-typeable verbs the plugin contributes, in the same form as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"game’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":". Defaults to empty. Merged with the host’s verbs and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"built-in table under the same last-wins policy."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"verbs"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto10SyntaxRuleV","text":"SyntaxRule"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"verbs","defaultImplementations":1,"required":true,"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin\/verbs","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin\/verbs"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Rules":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Rules","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected rules of a game, declared in one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" block. Large games"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compose: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var rules: Rules { cloakRules; barRules }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/rules","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/AddingCustomVerbs":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Adding Custom Verbs","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Teach the parser words the built-in table doesn’t know."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/addingcustomverbs"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin/rules":{"type":"topic","defaultImplementations":1,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin\/rules","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin\/rules","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"rules"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto5RulesV","text":"Rules"}],"title":"rules","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-contained, world-scoped rules the plugin adds without needing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"anything from the host. Defaults to empty. Rules that must reference the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host’s own entities are exposed as parameterized methods instead."}],"required":true},"doc://Gnusto/s8SendableP":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/s8SendableP","title":"Swift.Sendable","type":"unresolvable"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContents","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"importable unit of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}]},"doc://Gnusto/s16SendableMetatypeP":{"type":"unresolvable","title":"Swift.SendableMetatype","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/s16SendableMetatypeP"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}]}}}